{"lemma":"طِينُ","slug":"طِينُ","root":"ط.#.ن","root_slug":"ط-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-_-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طِين","root":"طين","pos":"N","occurrence_count":12},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n27486"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wet or sticky soil, clay, loam; mud"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ṭīn- (“clay”), and considered by some a borrowing from Classical Syriac ܛܝܼܢܵܐ (ṭīnā). Cognate with Akkadian 𒅎 (ṭīdum) and Hebrew טִיט (ṭiṭ)."},"ipa":["/tˤiːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27486","headword_ar":"طِينٌ","root":"Tyn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word of well-known meaning, (S, Msb, K, TA,) of which ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAnN","text_ar":"طَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. var.; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clay, earth, mould, soil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mud:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, KL, &c.:) it differs in different layers, or strata, of the earth; the best is the pure, unmixed with sand, remaining after the subsiding of the waters; and the best of this is that of Egypt, which has a peculiar property of preventing plague, or pestilence, and the corruption of water into which it is thrown: it is of several sorts; among which are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~iynu Almaxotuwmu","text_ar":"الطِّينُ المَخْتُومُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Terra sigillata,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lemnian earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~iynu AlA^aromaniY~u","text_ar":"الطِّينُ الاَرْمَنِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Armenian bole"},{"kind":"text","text":"], &c.: (TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiynapN","text_ar":"طِينَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a more particular signification, (S, Msb,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion, thereof,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) [as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of clay"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing of the kind termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sak~","text_ar":"صَكّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like are sealed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahowapu AlT~iyni","text_ar":"شَهْوَةُ الطِّينِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The longing for clay; a sort of malacia"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~aADN","text_ar":"حُمَّاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu AlT~iyni","text_ar":"اِبْنُ الطِّينِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Adam."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]}]}}